# Finding 060
- Severity: Low
- Pattern type: AI slop; Repeated `createRepository` boilerplate in app modules
- File + line(s): `apps/jskit-value-app/server/modules/alerts/index.js:31-35`, `apps/jskit-value-app/server/modules/billing/index.js:6-10`, `apps/jskit-value-app/server/modules/health/index.js:15-19`, `apps/jskit-value-app/server/modules/history/index.js:19-23`, `apps/jskit-value-app/server/modules/projects/index.js:29-33`, `apps/jskit-value-app/server/modules/settings/index.js:31-35`, `apps/jskit-value-app/server/modules/social/index.js:18-22`
- Why it can drift/fail: Each module defines the same `createRepository()` wrapper that just returns `{ repository }`. If repository exposure changes, every module must be updated manually.
- Concrete impact: Boilerplate repetition and higher chance of missed updates across modules.
- Exact remediation: Provide a shared helper (e.g., `createRepositoryExport(repository)`) or a module factory to standardize this pattern.

## Resolution
- Summary: introduced a shared `createRepositoryExport` helper and used it to standardize repository exports in app server modules.
